Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.91,0:16:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It comes from neurophysiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.19,0:16:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget the author's name now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.40,0:16:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's in the book I'm working on currently.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.32,0:16:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,By declaration and by commitment,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.08,0:16:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,you neurologically set up an attention set of priority.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.38,0:16:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Priority of attention set, you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.50,0:16:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Because options are coming forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.08,0:17:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You have like cascades of levels of options.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.63,0:17:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Cascades of levels of options.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.23,0:17:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the likelihood of you're making this choice
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.25,0:17:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than this choice?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.75,0:17:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,This brings up the whole question of free will.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.41,0:17:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Because by intention set,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.78,0:17:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the advanced physics of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.94,0:17:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,is the oftener you make this choice,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.98,0:17:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the greater the chance of success,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.14,0:17:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the greater mathematically the likelihood
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.20,0:17:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that you will make it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.54,0:17:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,In everyday lingo, we call it character formation
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.43,0:17:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and habit formation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.32,0:17:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Neurologically, you actually set up preferences
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.25,0:17:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,of priorities of dominations of attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.89,0:17:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's called attention set.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.34,0:17:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So by declaration and commitment to a spiritual goal
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.73,0:17:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and to a spiritual way of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.10,0:17:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,you prioritize choices.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.26,0:17:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You prioritize choices.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.89,0:17:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Having done that,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.15,0:17:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,it's less likely that you will choose to hate this guy
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.71,0:17:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's more likely you will try to understand him
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.80,0:18:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and forgive him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.85,0:18:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.95,0:18:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So attention set, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.32,0:18:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like you're setting your compass to be sensitive.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.76,0:18:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So choice is then free will.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.69,0:18:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,How does free will come about?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.99,0:18:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,There's all kinds of loony linear arguments about free will
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.49,0:18:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,that doesn't exist, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.84,0:18:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It ignores the fact that preference sets up a likelihood
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.43,0:18:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and advanced theoretical physics,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.58,0:18:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's what we're doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.00,0:18:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's the same thing with quantum mechanics.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.85,0:18:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a name for it in the name,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.79,0:18:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget it at the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.20,0:18:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But the more often you choose a certain sporadic event,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.85,0:18:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the more likely that will not be sporadic,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.94,0:18:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the more likely it will begin to reach.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.24,0:18:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called the Zeno effect, I think, something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.94,0:18:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That may be incorrect.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.85,0:18:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay to make a mistake, you know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.92,0:18:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Benevolence towards self and others.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.85,0:18:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I get the,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.73,0:19:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I get the blogger things, too, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.54,0:19:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Ooh, I'm paid so-and-so, you said so-and-so,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.89,0:19:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and so-and-so, and so-and-so.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.97,0:19:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, they gotcha, I gotcha, I gotcha, I gotcha.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.55,0:19:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you got me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.24,0:19:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Benevolence, that is the way of the human ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.66,0:19:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So how do you look at nasty bloggers with benevolence?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.03,0:19:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Attention set is the old-fashioned term for that
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.31,0:19:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,out of Eastern traditions is mindfulness.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.38,0:19:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What does mindfulness mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.01,0:19:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It means that at all times, there's some,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.70,0:19:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,some aspect of, some aspect that is self-reflective
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.68,0:19:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and watching yourself and mindful
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.22,0:19:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,so that you know when you're off course.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.57,0:19:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You find yourself hating somebody, I hate that so-and-so,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.35,0:19:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and some aspect of mindfulness brings to your attention
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.94,0:19:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're wandering off the path.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.70,0:20:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So mindfulness is merely a constant self-awareness,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.53,0:20:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,self-criticalness of where you are,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.31,0:20:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,like where we are in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.11,0:20:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,How much time do I have?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.52,0:20:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, good.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.34,0:20:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so in order to accomplish these things,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.08,0:20:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,then it's helpful to surrender
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.13,0:20:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,because you can pull out big blocks
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.41,0:20:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and get rid of all kinds of problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.56,0:20:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You see that the opposite of truth is not falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.73,0:20:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The opposite of truth is really narcissism.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.88,0:20:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really narcissism that's the opposite of truth
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.24,0:20:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,because how does falsehood arise?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.98,0:20:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It comes from worshiping the wonderful me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.86,0:20:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Having me at the center of the stage
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.17,0:20:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is the whole difficulty.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.00,0:20:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the ego juices every positionality
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.91,0:20:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to get what it can for wonderful, wonderful me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.42,0:21:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so renunciation,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.86,0:21:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,there's the pathway of renunciation.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.30,0:21:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Renunciation is a lifestyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.91,0:21:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You can leave the world and join an ashram
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.24,0:21:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and lead a devoted lifestyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.45,0:21:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Renunciation, to me, is a lifestyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.36,0:21:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,To me, it's internal.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.79,0:21:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not renouncing the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.77,0:21:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's renouncing the ego's attachment
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.00,0:21:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and gains from the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.11,0:21:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And yeah, I think you have to be more evolved
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.70,0:21:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,to be a renunciate and remain in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.70,0:21:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,than to withdraw from the world
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.57,0:21:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,because the world is always challenging.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.94,0:21:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The world is always tempting you to go out there
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.14,0:21:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,with a positionality and to renounce positionalities,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.40,0:21:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to be detached from the world means
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.00,0:21:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,to renounce all positionalities.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.58,0:22:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, a thing is what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.63,0:22:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,This snake, if he bites you, will kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.60,0:22:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have any position about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.08,0:22:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't make any claims about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.50,0:22:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It just is.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.59,0:22:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I avoid making any claims, if possible,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.51,0:22:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,except that I avoid making claims.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.45,0:22:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The intention is to reflect essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.13,0:22:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the intention, to reflect essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.02,0:22:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can make a commitment, with all your heart, to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.63,0:22:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You can make a commitment without making a claim.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.28,0:22:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And the funniest one is when somebody accused me
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.00,0:22:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of purposely committing a falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.36,0:22:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And I said, yes, I've written all these books
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.60,0:22:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and given a zillion lectures all over the world
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.47,0:22:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,on how to tell truth from falsehood,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.95,0:22:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and now I'm going to get in front of the audience
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.23,0:22:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and make a false claim.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.02,0:22:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to tell the real from the bogus,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.52,0:22:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and now I'm going to sell them bogus diamonds, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.25,0:23:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.56,0:23:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't mean you can't make an error.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.21,0:23:04.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course you can make an error.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.34,0:23:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So fearfulness, emotionalism, and the drama.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.30,0:23:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So what we watch all the time is people juicing the drama
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.73,0:23:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,out of victimhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.47,0:23:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my God, isn't that sickening, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.61,0:23:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Every tragedy has somebody out there on the TV land
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.03,0:23:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,juicing it and giving it a political twist
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.50,0:23:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,one way or the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.96,0:23:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Tragedy comes into everyone's life, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.03,0:23:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody lost one member of the family.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.25,0:23:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Good luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.61,0:23:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I've lost them all.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.72,0:23:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Good luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.75,0:23:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Emotionalism and the drama of victimhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.22,0:23:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so you see how it plays into the narcissism,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.03,0:24:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and so you see narcissistic indulgence.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.51,0:24:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't live by the opinions of others,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.72,0:24:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,but you should respect them.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.97,0:24:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I respect the opinions of others.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.76,0:24:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It means I don't have to agree with them,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.93,0:24:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,nor do I have to detract from them,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.69,0:24:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,but as a teacher, I do have to point out
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.63,0:24:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the downside of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.00,0:24:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're a couple of degrees off-compass,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.03,0:24:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that's not much in the short run,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.38,0:24:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,but as the miles go by, a couple of degrees off the compass,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.48,0:24:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,you're gonna end up in a different port
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.22,0:24:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,than the one you're headed for.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.70,0:24:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So mindfulness, then, is just watching your compass
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.57,0:24:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,to say, am I still on course?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.94,0:24:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Competitiveness, our society thrives on that, of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.90,0:24:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,because you can win,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.88,0:24:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's a big gain, and especially by being right.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.31,0:24:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And being right makes you feel very important.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.46,0:24:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And because you're right and you're important,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.50,0:24:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore, you wish to control others and change them,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.01,0:24:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,because you are special.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.90,0:25:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, children now are taught to express themself.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.16,0:25:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was young, I was taught not to express yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.25,0:25:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,My mother would say,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.29,0:25:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,if I had taken my sister in the streetcar,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.90,0:25:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was the dutiful, obsessive-compulsive,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.51,0:25:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,mindful in this one, and she was more wild, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.03,0:25:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So she'd run up and down the streetcar thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.77,0:25:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and I would sit in my seat and pretend I didn't know her,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.20,0:25:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,that I wasn't with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.74,0:25:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd just pretend I didn't even know who she was.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.77,0:25:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Too embarrassed.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.22,0:25:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So the idea of changing others,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.94,0:25:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think you can change others.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.40,0:25:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I think you can tell them how you see it,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.50,0:25:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and then it's up to them,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.59,0:25:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,because you can't control them.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.00,0:25:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So letting go, wanting to control other people,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.51,0:26:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,or change them, or make them different than they are,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.57,0:26:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,of course, is doomed to defeat.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.53,0:26:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, good luck across the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.92,0:26:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,now trying to change others and control them,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.11,0:26:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,because we're right, because we're important,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.98,0:26:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and thereby we'll gain and win.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.68,0:26:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.05,0:26:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,better, I can see, yeah, that's right, uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.81,0:26:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, in a couple thousand years, maybe, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.38,0:26:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Control others, change others.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.09,0:26:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And being special.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.29,0:26:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So all this kind of gain is to become special.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.85,0:26:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Specialness in relationships,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.42,0:26:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,specialness in positions, titles, possessions.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.55,0:26:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Lurking in the background is constant thinkingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.16,0:26:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Constant thinkingness, and of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.74,0:26:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,when we talked about meditation,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.18,0:26:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and contemplation, but especially meditation,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.61,0:26:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the difficulty is how to get beyond thinkingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.51,0:27:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And you do that when you notice that underneath
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.72,0:27:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,all the noise and the talk and the verbalization
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.03,0:27:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that's going on in the mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.96,0:27:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,there is an infinite stillness and silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.19,0:27:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of just watching the waves on the top of the ocean,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.34,0:27:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,wake up and realize that the ocean
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.06,0:27:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,goes down another thousand feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.21,0:27:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Down there, there aren't any waves, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.93,0:27:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So once you sense the infinite, profound silence,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.17,0:27:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,underneath thinkingness, you can learn how to live there.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.89,0:27:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the contemplative lifestyle,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.47,0:27:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,is to live in the infinite silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.36,0:27:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Without the infinite silence, you wouldn't be able
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.58,0:27:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,to know what you were thinking,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.78,0:27:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,nor could you even hear my voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.00,0:27:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because of the infinite silence,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.97,0:27:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,which is present in everybody in this room right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.33,0:27:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's mind right here is 99% silent.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.16,0:27:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,1% is listening to this voice and maybe thinking about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.16,0:27:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's better not to think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.11,0:27:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,don't think about this voice you could hear it with 1% of your mind but 99% of
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.22,0:28:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,you is not listening to me 99% of you are not paying attention to what's being
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.25,0:28:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,said at all it's just existing and being present and sensing itself as existence
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.76,0:28:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,it has an inner knowingness of existence and then the existence about the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.57,0:28:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,whatness the whatness is irrelevant if I switch the subject suddenly you won't
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.04,0:28:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,care really no you know because it hasn't really changed anything that
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.46,0:28:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,which you are repeats the same that which is still silent the presence
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.96,0:28:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,within is untouched by the linear because it's nonlinear so you learn to
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.50,0:28:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,identify with that underneath the thinkingness and you let go of the idea
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.70,0:28:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,of a personal independent self that is causing things you can let go of the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.25,0:28:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,idea of causation altogether as an illusion it's a very egotistical
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.61,0:28:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,illusion and then it's projected into the world because you think in terms of
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.57,0:28:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,cause-effects
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.88,0:28:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you think in terms of cause-effects
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.92,0:29:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,causality you see causality out there that's just your own ego projecting
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.79,0:29:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,itself into the world there's no causality out there each
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.51,0:29:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,thing is becoming what it is nothing is causing it become that it's happening
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.16,0:29:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,because it has the potential to express itself like that that's what you're
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.85,0:29:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,doing right yes it's expressing itself as it
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.65,0:29:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,autonomously expresses itself the personal self doesn't have
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.06,0:29:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,everything to do with it. What do I care whether the hand goes that way or this way? I don't have
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.76,0:29:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,any stake in it, do I? No gain, no pain. It can do whatever it likes. Sometimes it's funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.51,0:29:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have anything to do with it. If you look at your own ego that way, you can become
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.23,0:29:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,compassionate about it. It just goes off like a little winged thing doing whatever it does.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.50,0:30:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You can have compassion towards your own ego and stop seeing it as an enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.20,0:30:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What I disagree with in The Course in Miracles in the textbook, and the reason it calibrates
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.68,0:30:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,lower than the workbook, is the textbook is introducing a different voice. It's not the
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.07,0:30:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,same voice as the workbook. This other voice then sees the ego as an enemy, talks out rants
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.53,0:30:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and rages and so on. Yes, that's correct in a certain way, but it sets up a duality
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.31,0:30:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,with the ego as your enemy. The ego is not your enemy. The ego is a little wild little dog,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.07,0:30:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and all you have to do is make it friendly.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.96,0:30:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not house trained.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.46,0:30:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what you do is you adopt your ego like a pet.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.42,0:30:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Your little pet gets angry, it gets jealous.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.14,0:30:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.42,0:30:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You're jealous. He's got a bigger, nicer, newer car.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.03,0:31:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,She's got more diamonds.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.60,0:31:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,They live in a bigger house.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.72,0:31:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You got a higher salary.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.90,0:31:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Better title.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.16,0:31:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,More handsome.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.25,0:31:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Good looking. Athletic. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.99,0:31:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of all the things you can be jealous about.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.99,0:31:15.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't be more jealous than you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.33,0:31:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just you're too dumb to realize all the things that they are ahead of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.33,0:31:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't even know they're ahead of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.63,0:31:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got more kids than you.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.63,0:31:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,He can jump higher.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.63,0:31:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,There's all kinds of stuff you're missing that you could really be jealous about.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.63,0:31:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The same with being special.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.40,0:31:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.40,0:31:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you see the purpose of a sense of humor.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.75,0:31:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,As you begin to take the ego with a sense of humor.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.77,0:31:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's the little animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.77,0:31:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,As we've traced the evolution of the ego from the beginning of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.77,0:31:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It's interested in survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.77,0:31:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It's interested in territorial gain.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.77,0:31:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,When you listen to the world leaders right now, you don't know if they're talking about dogs or wolves.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.77,0:32:00.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What are they talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.91,0:32:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to expand our territory and take over your territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.64,0:32:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And kill this tribe so that our tribe.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.64,0:32:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Can have your territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.64,0:32:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is wolf talk, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.64,0:32:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What does that calibrate about?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.64,0:32:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,70? 80?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.64,0:32:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the level of a primitive animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.33,0:32:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll spray my scent here.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.19,0:32:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,This is my hunting range.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.98,0:32:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the president of Iran.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.08,0:32:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Israel will die.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.78,0:32:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hysterical.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.46,0:32:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That's left brain animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.69,0:32:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You see what?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.69,0:32:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.69,0:32:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if you're going to try and convince people.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.69,0:32:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,To convince them about benevolence, forgiveness.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.54,0:32:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What about forgiveness and benevolence?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.54,0:33:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.54,0:33:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.82,0:33:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Thinkingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.82,0:33:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.89,0:33:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the necessities.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.89,0:33:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,To put in the necessary effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.89,0:33:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We said mindfulness.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.89,0:33:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Mindfulness means being willing to put forth the energy to be watchful of yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.89,0:33:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And know when you're off course.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.77,0:33:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the willingness to spot your defects of character.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.77,0:33:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And the willingness to change them.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.77,0:33:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Admit them.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.77,0:33:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Admit your.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.77,0:33:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the 12 steps is willing to admit your shortcomings.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.14,0:33:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And ask God for help to overcome them.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.39,0:33:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't say we ignore our shortcomings.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.39,0:33:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Or made a big deal out of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.39,0:33:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It just said we noticed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.39,0:33:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That we always take more cookies than anybody else at the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.54,0:33:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to go into a guilt spasm about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.71,0:34:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So that does take some effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.71,0:34:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,To be watchful of yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.71,0:34:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And see areas where you can improve.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.71,0:34:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You do this out of gratitude to God for your creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.71,0:34:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The same reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.71,0:34:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,When you look at the great cathedrals in Europe.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.84,0:34:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And you realize.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.84,0:34:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,A man spent an entire lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.84,0:34:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Carving this one pulpit let's say.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.84,0:34:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,One entire lifetime was spent.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.84,0:34:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.84,0:34:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Because his devotion to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.84,0:34:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,His thankfulness for his own creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.84,0:34:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Expresses itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.84,0:34:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,In this expressive way.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.84,0:34:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It's his worship of God that he expresses.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.73,0:34:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Through excellence.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.73,0:34:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,For God he does the most painstaking excellence possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.73,0:34:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,When you look at the great windows.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.82,0:34:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,In the great cathedrals.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.96,0:34:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,There was one cathedral.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.96,0:34:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That they want to clean this window.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.96,0:34:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,To take down this stained glass window.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.96,0:35:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And clean it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.96,0:35:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Costs 1.5 million dollars.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.96,0:35:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Costs a couple million dollars.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.78,0:35:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,To take down these giant stained glass windows.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.78,0:35:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Take them all apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.78,0:35:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Clean them.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.78,0:35:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Reassemble them.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.78,0:35:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Put them back up.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.78,0:35:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,One and a half million dollars.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.01,0:35:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I was going to put ten in the plate.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.51,0:35:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.96,0:35:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What good is ten against a million?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.34,0:35:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,How is that going to help?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.57,0:35:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Is he going to buy a Kleenex.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.57,0:35:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,To blow his nose while he's doing it?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.57,0:35:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The enormity of man's effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.01,0:35:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,To express his devotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.01,0:35:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,To God.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.01,0:35:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Is staggering when you see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.01,0:35:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And it is a great spiritual experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.17,0:35:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,When you visit the great cathedrals.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.17,0:35:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The Washington National Cathedral is the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.17,0:35:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Or when you visit a place like in Sedona.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.28,0:35:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Chapel of the Holy Cross.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.28,0:35:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Knocked me out first time I saw it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.28,0:35:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And I spent many a night all night there.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.46,0:36:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,All by myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.46,0:36:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,In those days.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.46,0:36:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,They left the candles lighted at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.46,0:36:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,They let the music run at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.46,0:36:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And they did not lock the doors.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.46,0:36:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So you could go into the Chapel of the Holy Cross.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.07,0:36:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,After all the tourists had leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.07,0:36:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,After dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.46,0:36:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And there'd be no one there.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.46,0:36:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You had the whole chapel to yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.94,0:36:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,All night long.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.94,0:36:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It was fantastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.94,0:36:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,In the meantime.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.94,0:36:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,In the background.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.94,0:36:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,There was this beautiful music.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.94,0:36:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And the flickering candles.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.94,0:36:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And the silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.94,0:36:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It was stunning.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.38,0:36:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't calibrated that chapel recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.38,0:36:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.38,0:36:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And there I had some ecstatic experiences.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.38,0:36:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I went into the state of ecstasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.38,0:36:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Existing.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.38,0:36:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Existing.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.21,0:36:48.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Beyond ecstasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.21,0:36:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Beyond ecstasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.21,0:36:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,This too has to be surrendered to the old Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.21,0:36:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So as exquisite as it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.42,0:36:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You surrender the ecstasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.61,0:37:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And then when the ecstasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.42,0:37:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,When you've surrendered that to the old Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.42,0:37:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's replaced by an infinite peace that is beyond ecstasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.26,0:37:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The selfless service.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.42,0:37:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Is of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.42,0:37:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,A great way.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.42,0:37:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And an actual way.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.42,0:37:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's very, done in America, America is the most beneficent, is the most, what do you call it, philanthropic nation on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.28,0:37:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the most philanthropic nation on earth, in fact, probably of all of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.65,0:37:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,There are many other countries on the other side of the world that don't give anything to any humanitarian effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.55,0:37:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And we outdo the whole world.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.61,0:37:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,America puts out more than all the rest of the nations of the world, the UN, all the members of the UN put together don't equal what America, philanthropic givingness of America.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.44,0:38:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So those who say, you're going to be little America, I say, yeah, who else is looking after Asia and Africa, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.30,0:38:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,America gives more than all the rest of the nations in the UN put together.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.88,0:38:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,All of them, all 188 don't match what America puts out.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.28,0:38:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.71,0:38:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So selfless service, then, is time honored.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.32,0:38:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Inner honesty, that has to do with mindfulness.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.13,0:38:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Taking your personal inventory.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.82,0:38:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So part of one's prayers at the end of the day can be taking one's inner inventory, not in order to feel guilt, because guilt is a self-indulgence.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.38,0:38:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Guilt is narcissistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.65,0:38:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you ever realize that?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.73,0:38:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you get that?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.19,0:38:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,How guilty is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.11,0:38:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You know?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.92,0:38:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Guilt is narcissistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.15,0:38:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't wallow in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.07,0:38:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And, you know, it's just me, me, oh, how guilty I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.48,0:38:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the big me again.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.94,0:38:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The big, guilt is the big me.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.71,0:38:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So you have to be willing to let go of guilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.76,0:39:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Inner honesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.42,0:39:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Responsibility is part of mindfulness.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.55,0:39:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Part of mindfulness is with inner honesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.67,0:39:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,At least once a day, you take an inner inventory.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.44,0:39:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Mindfulness, you have an inner inventory going all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.36,0:39:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The minute you're somewhat off, you already feel that you're off.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.44,0:39:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,As you're taking responsibility for your own consciousness, the inner silence is what we talked about before, below all the thinkingness, below all this thinkingness, and all the glamour and conflict, is an inner silence, and as you evolve, you identify that that is who you are, and the inner silence then begins to manifest as a radiance, like a light coming up inside of yourself, a silent light that illuminates.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.07,0:39:48.21,Default,,0,0,0,,This is illumination.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.01,0:39:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It has.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.63,0:39:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It has no linear content.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.05,0:39:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just an illumination.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.69,0:40:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So the higher states of consciousness are called illumination because the subjective experience is that of a light coming forth from within oneself, and you realize that you're experiencing yourself with a capital S.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.01,0:40:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,There's an alignment with peace instead of drama, how people live off drama instead of peace, and will reject peace at any cost in order to keep the drama going because the ego feeds off drama.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.50,0:40:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.67,0:40:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.78,0:40:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.80,0:40:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.82,0:40:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And in the silence, you realize that witnessing and observing is going on all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.05,0:40:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So the mindfulness, the mindfulness is partly and eventually becomes the impersonal witness observer.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.25,0:40:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The observer and the witness notices those things without being necessarily termed the personal I.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.11,0:40:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, it's not exactly the personal I, and this is the easiest position towards enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.28,0:41:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's to withdraw from the arena, the movie, the drama, ask yourself, how do I know what's going on in the movie in my mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.44,0:41:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's because you're witnessing and observing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.55,0:41:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you can let go the identification with the content of consciousness and realize that that's which I call I.
