Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.98,0:42:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, then positionality, not attachment.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.05,0:42:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We talked about the pathway of negation, not attachment.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.80,0:42:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Renunciation means to stop being attached to looking.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.82,0:43:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,For gain, looking for payoff, et cetera, from all these linear positionalities, it negates, negates the reality of such things.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.42,0:43:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, the Buddha taught that originally, you know, all is transitory.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.76,0:43:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you become attached to that, which is transitory, you will bring about suffering and pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.05,0:43:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The way out of suffering is to is to non attachment, to let go your attachment to the delinear.
