Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.59,0:49:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You pick out somebody.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.17,0:49:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't see them.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.36,0:49:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, what is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.48,0:49:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.84,0:49:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.67,0:49:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that is the how-to of surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.03,0:50:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm, relinquishment.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.94,0:50:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It means learning how to become yin.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.23,0:50:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,How to surrender means to submit to God's will.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.53,0:50:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It means to stop resisting.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.00,0:50:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a technique that each energy or thought as you rise, you surrender to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.48,0:50:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you surrender?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.36,0:50:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That's sort of strange, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.76,0:50:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you ever float?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.13,0:50:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, there's swimming.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.21,0:50:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And then there's floating.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.48,0:50:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And so you float with no struggle.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.01,0:50:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You stop struggling.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.26,0:50:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,If you constantly surrender, what you're surrendering is the leading edge of the experiencer.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.23,0:50:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We said the ego rises through evolution for life to survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.23,0:50:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't have any source of energy within itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.71,0:50:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to sense what is edible and not edible.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.50,0:50:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,A little amoeba.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.19,0:51:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If it eats the wrong thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.51,0:51:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,he will stop being an amoeba.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.78,0:51:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll be an ex-amoeba.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.65,0:51:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So one of the first things he has to learn is truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.23,0:51:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So truth from falsehood is intrinsic.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.28,0:51:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, the newest research is that it's intrinsic to the mammalian kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.65,0:51:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It is hardwired.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.01,0:51:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,If you make the right choice, you survive and prosper.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.65,0:51:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you make the wrong choice, you get eliminated.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.61,0:51:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's not moralistic, but to be correct and not correct,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.28,0:51:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that which constantly chooses,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.07,0:51:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,incorrectness no longer survives.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.17,0:51:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So truth from falsehood is innate biologically,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.03,0:51:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,anatomically, and neurophysiologically.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.55,0:51:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Without it, you can't live.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.78,0:51:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,What was the question?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.51,0:51:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.63,0:52:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the Beatles' song, Let It Be.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.46,0:52:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, all right, Let It Be, it calibrates extremely high.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.53,0:52:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember when it came out,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.69,0:52:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Let It Be, the Stones quickly countered with Let It Bleed.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.34,0:52:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.63,0:52:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if you calibrate Let It Be compared to Let It Bleed,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.28,0:52:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,let's see what the Beatles saw.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.75,0:52:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Let It Be, we have permission to do Let It Be.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.36,0:52:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Let It Be is over 480, 500, 499, 500, 499, 49,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.44,0:52:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Let It Be, Let It Be.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.67,0:52:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Beatles were quite erudite, and they went their individual ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.51,0:52:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Stones hung together.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.98,0:52:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.57,0:52:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.05,0:52:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,like a team you know a team survival team so surrendering means to relinquish
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.15,0:53:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,to God's will and it's the actually when you think of it is the easiest thing in
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.09,0:53:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the world to do and that's why it's so difficult to let go resisting to become
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.11,0:53:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,very yin you know as I say you know yang is like so in yin is like so to allow to
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.90,0:53:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,allow is in his surrender thy will O Lord not mine if God's will is that it
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.98,0:53:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,heals then it heals if God's will is for it not to heal it won't heal so you can
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.84,0:53:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,only do so much and within a certain level
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.30,0:53:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and the
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.48,0:53:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,rest of
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.50,0:53:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,rest of
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.55,0:53:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,of
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.65,0:53:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,rest of
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.69,0:53:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Rest is up to divine providence, which a more sophisticated person discerns as karmic trends,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.09,0:54:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore what you think is a negative experience may well be the undoing of negative
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.26,0:54:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.26,0:54:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've given you some personal examples of going through surgery without anesthesia,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.17,0:54:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and during the middle of it recall the exact experience in a previous lifetime that brought
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.69,0:54:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,forth this karmic consequence, and so you accept then that God's grace is expressing
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.23,0:54:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,itself as allowing you to recover spiritually from the damage that you did to yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.28,0:54:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,People in hell do not have that option, that's why you don't want to go there.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.76,0:54:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we have the option by good actions to undo the consequences of bad actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.78,0:54:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We see it expressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.84,0:55:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, in sizable portions of the population, sizable, you know, sizable, great numbers
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.38,0:55:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,of people did horrendous things for many, many centuries, thousands of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.67,0:55:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Great hordes of people did horrible things, did they not?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.50,0:55:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And now we see horrible things happening, you know, to great hordes of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.26,0:55:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And mankind's been at war 93% of the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.21,0:55:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The other 7%, I never did get a chance to find out what he was up to.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.17,0:55:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,No good of some kind, no doubt.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.17,0:55:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't war, but it was probably something else just as bad, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.28,0:55:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So the evolution of mankind has been.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.00,0:55:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So out of gratitude for the willingness to surrender then is the willingness to worship
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.92,0:55:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,God by virtue of the expression of creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.84,0:56:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That every phenomena is an expression of the unfolding of creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.36,0:56:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, to surrender to it is, you know, the old saying, the reed that resists
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.59,0:56:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the stream breaks, and the reed that bends with the stream.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.50,0:56:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So you follow the Wu way, you follow the way of the wisdom, and you bend with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.55,0:56:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So if the regime is totalitarian, you blend with the totalitarianism.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.84,0:56:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You know?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.84,0:56:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.26,0:56:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So whatever the regime is, you blend with it, and then you look for a way that you might
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.63,0:56:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,shift your balance in what you think is a more favorable direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.84,0:56:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Surrendering is extremely easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.98,0:56:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you can float in the water, anybody here doesn't know how to float?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.07,0:56:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,There probably are.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.07,0:56:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, liars, speak up.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.07,0:56:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, yeah, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.42,0:56:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,How to float.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.42,0:56:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,How to just go with the wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.78,0:57:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And allow yourself to be passive, passive, passive participant, and then surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.88,0:57:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So recovery from any illnesses requires surrendering your will to God, taking a moral inventory,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.73,0:57:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,asking for God's help, and the willingness to surrender that which is habitually injurious
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.26,0:57:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,or painful to yourself or others, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.40,0:57:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that sufficient?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.92,0:57:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's exercises.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.17,0:57:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And passivity.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.17,0:57:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You ever do these exercises where you have three people, person in the middle, there's
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.71,0:57:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,a person behind them, and you push them over, and he has to allow himself to be caught by
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.76,0:57:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the other person?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.36,0:57:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's a good practice to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.03,0:57:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,If you can't figure out how to surrender, you need two people, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.65,0:57:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And somebody pushes you this way, and the other person catches you.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.59,0:58:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And to allow yourself to be thrown about like a midget.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.61,0:58:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Midgets don't mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.55,0:58:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.19,0:58:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.19,0:58:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just the viewers think it's insulting to midgets.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.19,0:58:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Midgets don't feel that way at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.19,0:58:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It must be fun just to be thrown around.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.19,0:58:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine flying through the air and people are catching you.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.19,0:58:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it would be hilarious.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.53,0:58:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody else got anything else they want?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.53,0:58:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll hear some other things.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.53,0:58:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But let's have a vote for whatever subject you might like finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.28,0:58:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like for you to explain how we can do self-vocation and self-referencing.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.55,0:58:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I think it's a great question.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.55,0:58:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I think it's a great question.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.55,0:58:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I think it's a great question.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.55,0:58:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's a great question.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.55,0:58:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's a great question.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.55,0:58:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's a great question.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.55,0:58:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's a great question.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.55,0:58:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's a great question.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.84,0:58:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's a great question.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.84,0:58:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's a great question.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.84,0:58:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think it's a great question.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.84,0:58:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.84,0:58:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure what the question is.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.84,0:58:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.84,0:58:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it doesn't really sound like conflict.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.84,0:58:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Does it?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.84,0:58:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.84,0:58:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Belinda?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.84,0:58:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, how is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.84,0:58:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Just getting to the heart of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.84,0:58:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.84,0:58:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Good to be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.84,0:58:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Great.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.84,0:58:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I'mINTERPOSINGいて Gordon.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.84,0:58:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Roberto Garcia Saldana.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.84,0:58:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.84,0:58:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm youаетrabandobillia.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.84,0:58:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.84,0:58:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.23,0:58:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you come to the exercise on the wall?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.36,0:58:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.36,0:58:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Ok.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.36,0:58:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Koban?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.36,0:58:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.36,0:58:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,J lassen.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.36,0:58:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,LOL.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.61,0:59:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Well many of these things are non-verbal.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.76,0:59:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,As I said the contemplative lifestyle is one in which you see instead of acquiring knowledge
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.76,0:59:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,you can retreat and allow for revelation.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.05,0:59:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The major experiences of my life are all revelations.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.36,0:59:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They were preceded by let's say some great anguish within the ego, the mind, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.76,0:59:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But the experiences were all extremely yin.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.21,0:59:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It was all a matter of standing back and allowing that which is magnificent to reveal itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.96,0:59:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,None of it was acquisition.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.78,0:59:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no going from here to there or from this space to that space.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.09,0:59:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The willingness to let go of thinkingness, well that has to do with letting go of opinionation
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.65,0:59:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and you don't need it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.51,0:59:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need an opinion on anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.76,1:00:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember a friend of mine in recovery and he said,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.38,1:00:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,it suddenly dawned on me I don't have to have an opinion on everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.15,1:00:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, wow, what a relief, you don't have to have an opinion on everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.05,1:00:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact you don't have to have an opinion at all, you become the witness observer.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.69,1:00:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The witness observer just observes how it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.26,1:00:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This survives, this doesn't survive.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.40,1:00:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.86,1:00:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The leaves turn brown, the leaves fall off and acquiescence to God's will is nearly witnessing
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.53,1:00:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the unfoldment of evolution as creation.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.13,1:00:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Creation and evolution are one and the same thing and therefore allowing spontaneity.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.32,1:00:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is becoming the actuality of that which it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.17,1:00:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What anything means, what does anything mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.61,1:01:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything you can say about.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.19,1:01:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What a thing means is idiotic.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.78,1:01:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.65,1:01:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What a thing means is what it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.65,1:01:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you have to talk about it?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.32,1:01:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the meaning of this?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.59,1:01:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's spoken.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.88,1:01:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It speaks again.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.92,1:01:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.05,1:01:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that I use it for that doesn't mean that's what it means.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.90,1:01:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It means what it means to me, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:32.69,1:01:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what a thing means is identical with it's existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.09,1:01:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a very advanced, a very advanced, a very advanced technique.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.94,1:01:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.98,1:01:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.05,1:01:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,insight, a very advanced
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.73,1:01:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,philosophic, epistemological
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.38,1:01:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,knowingness, which is beyond
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.73,1:01:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,verbalization. It's really an awareness
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.90,1:01:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,that
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.05,1:01:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,everything is being what it is
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.90,1:01:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and its expression of its reality
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.96,1:01:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,is its meaning.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.90,1:01:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at the lovely curve
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.23,1:02:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,to the pattern. Look at the lovely
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.07,1:02:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,color of the green. Everything
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.07,1:02:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,is stunningly, perfectly
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.78,1:02:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,exactly what it is. It couldn't be
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.07,1:02:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,better than what it is. How could
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.19,1:02:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,it be better than what it is?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.69,1:02:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying? Put pebbles
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.71,1:02:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,on it and have it make music or what?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.44,1:02:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The perfect curve,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.36,1:02:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the perfect expression of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.92,1:02:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The room is just
Dialogue: 0,1:02:19.80,1:02:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,perfect the way it is, is it not?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.55,1:02:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,My shoes are perfect the way they are.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.23,1:02:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,My pants are perfect.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.92,1:02:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,My jacket's perfect. Everything's perfect
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.05,1:02:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.48,1:02:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't see as well.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.53,1:02:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That's perfectly
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.19,1:02:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,what it is. Perfectly what it is
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.69,1:02:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,is a
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.50,1:02:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,diminution
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.00,1:02:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,of
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.09,1:02:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,diminution of
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.11,1:02:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,being able to see out of one eye.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.82,1:02:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.86,1:02:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.13,1:02:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.78,1:02:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So what?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:50.09,1:02:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Like accepting
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.15,1:02:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,you have two ears, one nose, I mean
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.07,1:02:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,protoplasm
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.26,1:02:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,gets older. Should it
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.78,1:03:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,be that way? You see how
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.13,1:03:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,nonsensical it is to ask the question.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.78,1:03:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,What does it mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.86,1:03:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't mean anything. It just
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.03,1:03:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,is what it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.53,1:03:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Protoplasm is meant
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.51,1:03:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,to arise from
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.94,1:03:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that which arises, turns back to dust,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.94,1:03:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,does it not?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.07,1:03:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So what else?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.57,1:03:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Resignation. Resignation is the closest
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.55,1:03:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,thing I could get to it, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.86,1:03:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Hawkins, you say that
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.61,1:03:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to be a witness to positionality,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.82,1:03:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,how do I differentiate that
Dialogue: 0,1:03:36.07,1:03:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,from perception?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.23,1:03:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.53,1:03:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That is called my mind-melting charm,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.25,1:03:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,mind-do.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.34,1:03:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.65,1:03:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so letting go of the valuing
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.36,1:03:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of opinions. See, the ego gets
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.36,1:03:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,a lot of food out of it, out of having an opinion
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.36,1:03:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,about everything. If you're willing to
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.34,1:03:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,relinquish the juice out of
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.88,1:03:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,having an opinion and stop having
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.53,1:03:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,opinions, then you're content to
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.61,1:03:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,witness.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.17,1:04:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You witness the beauty
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.34,1:04:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of all creation.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.98,1:04:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So you retreat from the
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.25,1:04:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,thinker, the experiencer,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:09.21,1:04:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,you withdraw to
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.63,1:04:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that aspect of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.36,1:04:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,called witness. You're the
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.51,1:04:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,witness observer.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.61,1:04:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I witness this
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.98,1:04:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,curvaceous thing here.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.30,1:04:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have to have an opinion.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:22.84,1:04:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, I don't have to tell you that I think it's aesthetically
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.03,1:04:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,pleasing. I don't have to tell you that
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.71,1:04:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I like the color green.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.03,1:04:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,All that's unnecessary. That's just
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.78,1:04:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,conversation.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.67,1:04:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,In reality, you just look at it
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.98,1:04:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and you see it, but there's no comment.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.05,1:04:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't look at every
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.96,1:04:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,tree and stop and say, boy,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.90,1:04:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that is a nice tree and write a whole
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.92,1:04:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,essay on it. Then you go to the next
Dialogue: 0,1:04:46.07,1:04:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,tree and write an essay on that one. Then you see
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.96,1:04:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the mountain, you write an essay, and then you write an essay
Dialogue: 0,1:04:49.82,1:04:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,on the road, and then you're...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:51.30,1:04:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't write an essay on everything, so don't you
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.84,1:04:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,see how the pomposity of the
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.73,1:04:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,narcissism of the ego has
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.78,1:04:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,to express an opinion about
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.84,1:05:02.17,Default,,0,0,0,,everything? That's the disaster
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.17,1:05:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,of the
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.90,1:05:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,giggledom
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.94,1:05:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,empire. What is that? Gang people.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.71,1:05:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The talk-up
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.86,1:05:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,electronic world.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.09,1:05:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What do they call those things? Bloggers.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.98,1:05:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Bloggers. Bloggerism.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:17.00,1:05:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The blog site
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.98,1:05:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,is the world of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.19,1:05:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody asks any of those people to put
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.71,1:05:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,an effing thing up there.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.23,1:05:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the name of their website? It's called
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.90,1:05:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Me.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.07,1:05:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Wonderful Me.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:36.07,1:05:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Wonderful Me.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.05,1:05:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, beautiful, wonderful me.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:41.09,1:05:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what I think.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.73,1:05:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole world
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.88,1:05:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,waits with bated breath.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.69,1:05:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What does Morgenstein Schnuckenbarger
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.59,1:05:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,think about the
Dialogue: 0,1:05:52.46,1:05:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,president of Iran?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.76,1:05:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care what he thinks about the president of Iran.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.61,1:06:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The president of Iran
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.05,1:06:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't care what he thinks about the president of Iran.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.11,1:06:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't care what he thinks about the president of Iran.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.23,1:06:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither. Other than being wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:05.17,1:06:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Do I think
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.40,1:06:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,it's awful you should think you're wonderful?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.32,1:06:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,No. It's wonderful that you think you're wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.98,1:06:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The only way you can hit bottom.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.51,1:06:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So you eventually relinquish
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.13,1:06:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,opinionation and commentary
Dialogue: 0,1:06:27.69,1:06:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,because you see it's irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.23,1:06:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You're in the middle
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.07,1:06:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,of a giant, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.40,1:06:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,magnificent woods and everything is still
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.76,1:06:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and silent. Nothing needs
Dialogue: 0,1:06:38.57,1:06:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,your commentary.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:40.48,1:06:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The tree doesn't need you to say,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:42.07,1:06:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, what a beautiful tree.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.92,1:06:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The tree says,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.53,1:06:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,what an idiot.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.38,1:06:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What a beautiful
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.71,1:06:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,tree.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:52.46,1:06:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, what a beautiful
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.19,1:06:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,human.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.53,1:07:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing needs your
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.71,1:07:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,commentary.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:07.98,1:07:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you see
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.76,1:07:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,how superficial, how
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.21,1:07:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,irrelevant it is,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.82,1:07:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't quit it because it's wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.05,1:07:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You just see that it's worthless.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.86,1:07:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It has no value.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.80,1:07:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It has no value.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:21.71,1:07:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And that it's a disturbance.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:23.38,1:07:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So that you're preoccupied
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.15,1:07:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,with opinionation running across your mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.53,1:07:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you don't
Dialogue: 0,1:07:29.92,1:07:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,notice that the mind is really primarily
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.94,1:07:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,silent. You see?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.21,1:07:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Silent.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:37.42,1:07:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of nowhere comes a hand.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.42,1:07:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't cause it to do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.46,1:07:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't ask it to do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.26,1:07:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just suddenly a hand appears from nowhere
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.42,1:07:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and adjusts your microphone.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:50.67,1:07:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how wonderful the world is?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.15,1:07:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just perfect. Everything is concordant.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.44,1:07:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything interacts with complete perfection.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.90,1:07:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,As you relinquish
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.21,1:08:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,opinionation about everything,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.96,1:08:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the perfection of all.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:04.67,1:08:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.63,1:08:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The perfection of
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.51,1:08:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,all that exists shines forth.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.42,1:08:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,In one stunning instant,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.84,1:08:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,you see the absolute perfection
Dialogue: 0,1:08:14.42,1:08:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,of all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.78,1:08:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Shortly behind
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.72,1:08:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,seeing the perfection,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:20.00,1:08:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,you see the beauty of all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:23.56,1:08:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the divinity
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.60,1:08:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,of that which exists
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.43,1:08:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,shines forth as the essence
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.14,1:08:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,of existence itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.69,1:08:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is
Dialogue: 0,1:08:31.46,1:08:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,like overwhelming.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.22,1:08:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And if there were
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.06,1:08:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,any remaining thoughts, they disappear.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.14,1:08:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.42,1:08:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,what reveals itself
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.60,1:08:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,can only be described
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.35,1:08:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,as a wonderment.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.69,1:08:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,A wonderment of immense dimension.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.23,1:08:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like you've been
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.00,1:08:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,looking at it your whole lifetime
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.06,1:08:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and never realized what it was.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.22,1:08:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.89,1:09:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And suddenly, it's like the door is
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.01,1:09:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,open and the essence
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.44,1:09:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,of that which it is shines forth.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:07.90,1:09:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And the mind is silent
Dialogue: 0,1:09:09.90,1:09:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,thereafter.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:11.63,1:09:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing that can be said.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:15.03,1:09:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,A wonderment.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.85,1:09:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,A whole shipload of passengers
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.61,1:09:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,went into a wonderment.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.81,1:09:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We were going up.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:26.34,1:09:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The inside channel
Dialogue: 0,1:09:27.80,1:09:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,hadn't been away in three years.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:30.27,1:09:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I went to the Alaska Inland
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.00,1:09:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,whatchamacallit
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.38,1:09:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Inland Tour.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:36.38,1:09:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we come to
Dialogue: 0,1:09:39.09,1:09:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,a place called something arm.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:42.31,1:09:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Tracy's Arm, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.35,1:09:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:45.52,1:09:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,all around you are these incredible mountains
Dialogue: 0,1:09:47.65,1:09:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and the mystical
Dialogue: 0,1:09:48.61,1:09:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,clouds.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.02,1:09:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The clouds there just stay there.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:54.89,1:09:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,They stay there. A cloud just stays there like this.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:57.77,1:09:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And this whole
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.96,1:09:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,huge
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.43,1:10:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,ship stopped.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.27,1:10:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's stopped right in the middle.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:03.15,1:10:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And it slowly let itself go around
Dialogue: 0,1:10:05.73,1:10:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,like this because all the passengers
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.88,1:10:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,were like struck with awe.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:10.60,1:10:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like the incredible beauty
Dialogue: 0,1:10:12.56,1:10:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,of it finally got through
Dialogue: 0,1:10:14.25,1:10:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and the mind stopped thinking.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:16.84,1:10:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And everybody went into like a mystical state.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:19.46,1:10:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We calibrated that view
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.27,1:10:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,on Tracy's arm.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:23.06,1:10:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,There's 635, I think, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:25.64,1:10:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I don't think over 600 is
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.68,1:10:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,none of your bliss.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.31,1:10:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So, here's a whole ship with, I don't know,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.43,1:10:34.43,Default,,0,0,0,,a thousand people on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.43,1:10:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And everybody suddenly gets still.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:36.43,1:10:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And this giant ship slowly, slowly, slowly goes around.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:39.43,1:10:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And everybody goes into a state of wonderment
Dialogue: 0,1:10:42.43,1:10:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,at the incredible beauty.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.43,1:10:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And they probably wouldn't have done so
Dialogue: 0,1:10:47.63,1:10:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,except for the wisdom of the captain who stopped it.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:50.63,1:10:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,He was like, the captain was saying to you,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.63,1:10:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,look at the beautiful scene.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:57.63,1:10:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,He was French.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.63,1:10:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And he had a...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:59.63,1:11:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,At the end of everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.63,1:11:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And now we will stop at the ship
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.63,1:11:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and we will stay here for a few moments.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.63,1:11:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can see the beautiful view.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:15.02,1:11:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And there it was, like God's creation,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:18.02,1:11:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the divinity of all that's shown forth.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:20.02,1:11:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's shown forth at 635,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.02,1:11:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,which is pretty very high
Dialogue: 0,1:11:24.02,1:11:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,for just a physical expression.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:27.02,1:11:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:29.07,1:11:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the question.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:33.97,1:11:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Hawkins, I understand how you can consciously
Dialogue: 0,1:11:37.73,1:11:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,envision about what you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:42.65,1:11:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But what I was referring to,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:44.65,1:11:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the innate coloring that we have
Dialogue: 0,1:11:47.88,1:11:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,when we see a world through our own colored classes
Dialogue: 0,1:11:49.88,1:11:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that are determined by our upbringing,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:51.88,1:11:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,by our culture.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:52.88,1:11:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:53.88,1:11:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a matter of sophistication
Dialogue: 0,1:11:56.77,1:11:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,to transcend the current belief systems.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.35,1:12:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Or to not identify with them.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.69,1:12:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Not take a position about them.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:07.69,1:12:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You can say, I think that's correct.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:09.69,1:12:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And they say, are you willing to die for that?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:11.78,1:12:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,No, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:17.77,1:12:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,No, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:20.32,1:12:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what if America
Dialogue: 0,1:12:22.39,1:12:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,was still a colony of Great Britain?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:25.39,1:12:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So what?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:27.22,1:12:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What if it was?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:29.38,1:12:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What if this was still a British dominion?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:32.38,1:12:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:34.10,1:12:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Would the subway stop?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.10,1:12:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you stop going to work?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:38.14,1:12:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,People stop populating?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:39.14,1:12:41.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Having children?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.14,1:12:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, what if the Revolutionary War
Dialogue: 0,1:12:43.68,1:12:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,had never happened?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:45.68,1:12:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'd be British citizens.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:48.22,1:12:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd have pounds instead of dollars.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:52.13,1:12:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Life wouldn't change hardly at all, would it?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:55.22,1:12:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,No great deal, would it?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:58.09,1:13:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It satisfies our egotism that we're independent
Dialogue: 0,1:13:04.15,1:13:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,of the British Empire.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:06.77,1:13:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But it doesn't really matter.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:09.97,1:13:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, the only thing wrong with the British Empire
Dialogue: 0,1:13:12.50,1:13:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,is you got carried away with craziness
Dialogue: 0,1:13:14.50,1:13:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,George III.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:15.50,1:13:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:16.50,1:13:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't that there was a British Empire.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:18.50,1:13:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It was that it was abusive of its power.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:20.50,1:13:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Abusive, exploitive.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:22.50,1:13:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Had George III been a, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:26.19,1:13:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,like the Dalai Lama,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:28.19,1:13:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,we probably never would have revolted, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:33.19,1:13:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So let everything be.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:34.19,1:13:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So all the things that we die for,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:36.19,1:13:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,even when you recontextualize history,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.19,1:13:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,you say, well, what if it had been otherwise?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:42.19,1:13:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And probably nothing at all
Dialogue: 0,1:13:44.19,1:13:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,if it had been otherwise, you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:46.19,1:13:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.30,1:13:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:50.26,1:13:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Any other thing you want covered
Dialogue: 0,1:13:52.77,1:13:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we'll finish up any lecture material.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:55.96,1:13:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.65,1:14:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm curious if you could tell me about the soul.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:02.65,1:14:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Does that come directly from God
Dialogue: 0,1:14:04.65,1:14:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,or is it that the soul needs to evolve
Dialogue: 0,1:14:08.65,1:14:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's why some...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.65,1:14:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'll give you my understanding of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:13.65,1:14:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is, you know, not separated from God.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:17.65,1:14:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But because of its nature,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:21.69,1:14:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the arising of the ego
Dialogue: 0,1:14:23.69,1:14:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and the identification with that,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:26.85,1:14:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,you're asking about the soul,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:28.94,1:14:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,which is eternal.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.94,1:14:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:30.94,1:14:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So the soul is nonlinear itself intrinsically.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:33.94,1:14:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But I understand within the nonlinear
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.94,1:14:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,are energy fields that we call karmic
Dialogue: 0,1:14:39.94,1:14:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that are set up in the infinite field of consciousness itself
Dialogue: 0,1:14:45.18,1:14:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,as vibrational patterns.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.27,1:14:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, with consciousness research,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.27,1:14:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you're not limited to time, location or distance.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:56.50,1:14:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But was is now.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:58.50,1:15:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no separation in time.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:00.50,1:15:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no separation in place.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:03.50,1:15:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,All of reality is equally present
Dialogue: 0,1:15:07.22,1:15:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,at every single point within space,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:10.22,1:15:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,within creation.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:14.60,1:15:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,All that has ever existed
Dialogue: 0,1:15:16.85,1:15:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,in all of its expressions
Dialogue: 0,1:15:18.85,1:15:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout all of time,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:21.72,1:15:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,everywhere in the universe,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.72,1:15:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,exists at every single point.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:26.97,1:15:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.97,1:15:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:35.56,1:15:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,All that has ever existed
Dialogue: 0,1:15:37.56,1:15:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,in all of its expressions,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.56,1:15:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,anywhere in time or space,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:41.92,1:15:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is existent right now
Dialogue: 0,1:15:43.92,1:15:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and available everywhere in space.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:47.21,1:15:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, we can,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:50.21,1:15:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,with kinesiologic research,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:52.21,1:15:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrate everything Napoleon said
Dialogue: 0,1:15:54.21,1:15:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and thought, felt,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:56.21,1:15:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,all through his campaigns.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:59.86,1:16:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,How Napoleon felt
Dialogue: 0,1:16:00.86,1:16:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,before he entered the Great Pyramid
Dialogue: 0,1:16:02.86,1:16:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and what he thought and felt
Dialogue: 0,1:16:04.86,1:16:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,after he left the Great Pyramid.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:06.86,1:16:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And I meditated in the Great Pyramid
Dialogue: 0,1:16:08.86,1:16:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,myself all night long.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:12.78,1:16:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,When Napoleon thought and felt
Dialogue: 0,1:16:14.78,1:16:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,in the transformation,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:17.27,1:16:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,his realization
Dialogue: 0,1:16:19.27,1:16:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,that he was going to be defeated,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:21.27,1:16:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway, arose as he walked out
Dialogue: 0,1:16:23.34,1:16:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Great Pyramid.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:25.34,1:16:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can ask about that now.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:27.46,1:16:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,If we want to know anything about Napoleon,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:30.46,1:16:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,we can get every detail
Dialogue: 0,1:16:32.52,1:16:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of every instant leading up to that.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:34.52,1:16:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What he thought, what he felt,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:36.52,1:16:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,how it was resolved,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:38.52,1:16:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,what his karma was about that, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:42.19,1:16:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, you remember Napoleon
Dialogue: 0,1:16:44.19,1:16:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrated around 440 or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:46.19,1:16:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And then when he crowned himself Emperor,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:50.26,1:16:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,when he crowned himself Emperor,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:52.48,1:16:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,he dropped from 440 to, I forget,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:54.48,1:16:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,190 or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.64,1:16:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So he was,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:57.64,1:17:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,when he met the Duke of Wellington,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:01.89,1:17:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Napoleon was counting on his previous power
Dialogue: 0,1:17:04.93,1:17:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,at 440.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:06.93,1:17:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And he was a great, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:08.93,1:17:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,one of the greatest generals that ever lived.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:11.06,1:17:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Napoleon was extremely brilliant.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.06,1:17:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But when he crowned himself Emperor,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:17.44,1:17:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,then he fell from 440 to,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:20.80,1:17:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget what he was at the end.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:22.80,1:17:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And so when he met the Duke of Wellington,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:25.80,1:17:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,he calibrated much less than the Duke of Wellington.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:27.80,1:17:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The Duke of Wellington at the time was 420.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.80,1:17:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think Napoleon had dropped to 170 or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:32.80,1:17:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So how could Napoleon have dropped so dramatically?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.80,1:17:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Because all the leaders,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:37.98,1:17:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,all the emperors, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:40.89,1:17:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,were crowned by the Vatican,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:43.89,1:17:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,by the Pope,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:44.89,1:17:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,by virtue of the Lord Jesus Christ,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:46.89,1:17:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,through his representative on earth, the Pope.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:50.89,1:17:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So to allow yourself to be crowned by the Pope
Dialogue: 0,1:17:53.89,1:17:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,was in a way acknowledging your subservience to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:57.89,1:18:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Via the symbolism of the church and the Pope.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:00.89,1:18:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's really acknowledging the sovereignty of God.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:06.30,1:18:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,By the sovereignty of God,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:08.52,1:18:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you become the ruler of men.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:10.52,1:18:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So when Napoleon crowned himself,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:13.52,1:18:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,he was rejecting divinity as the source of authority.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:16.52,1:18:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And crowned himself the same as Nero had done.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:20.52,1:18:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And he crashed like Nero did.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:22.52,1:18:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So when he met the Duke of Wellington,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:24.52,1:18:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Napoleon was shocked because he was depending
Dialogue: 0,1:18:27.81,1:18:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,on his old expertise at calibration 440.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:32.81,1:18:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And instead he'd lost it.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:34.81,1:18:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So he now was at calibrated less than the Duke of Wellington.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:38.81,1:18:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course Napoleon, when he invaded Russia,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:45.31,1:18:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,made the fatal mistake of grandiosity.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:48.63,1:18:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And Hitler, who was a student of Napoleon,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.63,1:18:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,for the exactly same reason,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:53.63,1:18:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,turned around and made the identical mistake
Dialogue: 0,1:18:56.63,1:18:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,to invade Russia in the winter.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:58.63,1:18:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:59.63,1:19:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Grandiosity.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:01.63,1:19:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,To think you can have a war on two fronts
Dialogue: 0,1:19:03.63,1:19:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and invade Russia in the winter.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:05.65,1:19:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You could say,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:06.65,1:19:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,how could a man as brilliant as Napoleon be so stupid?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:09.65,1:19:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Because he had negated the source of his power
Dialogue: 0,1:19:13.65,1:19:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,as not God, but his own ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:16.65,1:19:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So therefore,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:18.65,1:19:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the opposite of divinity
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.65,1:19:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,is the narcissistic core of the ego,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:23.65,1:19:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,which we call the devil.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:24.65,1:19:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Because when it expresses itself,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:26.65,1:19:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,it's pretty unsavory
Dialogue: 0,1:19:28.72,1:19:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,in its mode of expression.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:30.72,1:19:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But the opposite of God
Dialogue: 0,1:19:31.72,1:19:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is the narcissistic core of the ego,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:33.72,1:19:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,which claims sovereignty on its own.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:36.72,1:19:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It claims sovereignty.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:39.72,1:19:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,If it doesn't claim innate sovereignty,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.72,1:19:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,it claims the authorization of sovereignty.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:45.72,1:19:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So in the name of God,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:47.72,1:19:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the worst and most horrendous things happen in our world.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:52.72,1:19:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Because once you say it's in the name of God,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:55.89,1:19:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,now there's no limits.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:56.89,1:19:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:57.89,1:20:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And the narcissistic core of the ego is sovereign.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:00.89,1:20:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So whether you're going to worship
Dialogue: 0,1:20:02.97,1:20:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,the narcissistic core of the ego or divinity
Dialogue: 0,1:20:05.97,1:20:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,is really what life is all about
Dialogue: 0,1:20:08.97,1:20:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,in its various expressions.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:09.97,1:20:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:10.97,1:20:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you didn't ask me that.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.42,1:20:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But yes, in the back.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:19.42,1:20:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Hawkins, regarding something that you wrote about
Dialogue: 0,1:20:24.06,1:20:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,in Truth vs. Falsehood,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:26.06,1:20:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,is it true that there is no such thing
Dialogue: 0,1:20:29.60,1:20:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,as extraterrestrial physical life?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:32.60,1:20:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Extraterrestrials?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:34.67,1:20:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you know, in terms of, like,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:38.81,1:20:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,UFO-type of extraterrestrials?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:40.81,1:20:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let's ask it now.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:42.81,1:20:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but he's talking about something different.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:49.09,1:20:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Extraterrestrials, as represented in the literary world,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:54.18,1:20:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,are fictitious.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:56.18,1:20:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I have, okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:05.72,1:21:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to ask about extraterrestrials.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.92,1:21:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Extraterrestrials.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.92,1:21:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:11.92,1:21:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,They are the product of imagination.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:13.92,1:21:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:14.92,1:21:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:15.92,1:21:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Extraterrestrials, as pictured,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.92,1:21:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,are imaginary.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:19.92,1:21:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:20.92,1:21:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,There are, however, entities living in other galaxies
Dialogue: 0,1:21:24.92,1:21:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and celestial systems.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:26.92,1:21:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:27.92,1:21:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:29.36,1:21:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So extraterrestrial meaning from our planet
Dialogue: 0,1:21:32.36,1:21:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,or extraterrestrial meaning, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:35.36,1:21:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,ooh-la-la kind of extraterrestrials.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:38.36,1:21:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:40.68,1:21:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:41.68,1:21:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And they're not visitors from other planets and all.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:44.26,1:21:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't have any in Sedona.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:52.26,1:21:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't allow them within the city limits.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:56.31,1:21:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,They've got five minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:57.35,1:21:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:58.35,1:22:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we're going to go to the questions and answers.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:00.35,1:22:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:01.93,1:22:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you speak on sexuality within the context
Dialogue: 0,1:22:05.93,1:22:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,of spiritual enlightenment?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.34,1:22:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Sexuality and enlightenment?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:11.34,1:22:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Within the context.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:13.38,1:22:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:17.77,1:22:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That has to do with the mammalian,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:21.22,1:22:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,with our genetic origin, you know, and evolution.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:27.22,1:22:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the mammalian kingdom,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:29.22,1:22:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the chromosomal patterns are necessary
Dialogue: 0,1:22:36.38,1:22:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,for the continuation of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:38.38,1:22:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,As far as the origination of it within consciousness itself,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:42.40,1:22:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the yin and yang of the universe,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:44.40,1:22:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,is of course expressed best in the eastern tradition
Dialogue: 0,1:22:52.30,1:22:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of yin and yang as merely the directions of energies.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:57.36,1:22:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The directions of energies.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:59.36,1:23:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And they look at it as impersonally.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:02.36,1:23:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, it's impersonal.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.36,1:23:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It becomes sexualized in the mammalian animal life kingdom,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:08.36,1:23:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,insects and other things.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:10.36,1:23:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the purpose of it?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:12.36,1:23:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no idea.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:13.36,1:23:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Getting married and having kids, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:14.36,1:23:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the purpose of it?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:19.36,1:23:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The fulfillment of the human potential.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:21.36,1:23:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't tell you the reason,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:23.36,1:23:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,because it has to do with divinity
Dialogue: 0,1:23:26.36,1:23:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,as the source of the origination of mankind and humankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:33.73,1:23:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The Garden of Eden supposedly was non-linear paradise.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:39.80,1:23:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Non-linear paradise.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:42.31,1:23:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,People say they don't, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:43.31,1:23:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Christianity doesn't believe in karma.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:45.31,1:23:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course they do.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:46.31,1:23:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think original sin is all about?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:48.31,1:23:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You read Genesis,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:49.31,1:23:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and in the Garden of non-linear paradise,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:53.31,1:23:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,temptation came in the form of curiosity,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:58.61,1:24:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and the curiosity, the innate curiosity of the child
Dialogue: 0,1:24:01.61,1:24:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,fell for the invitation of the snake
Dialogue: 0,1:24:04.61,1:24:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,to eat of the tree of good and evil,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:07.61,1:24:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the bush of good and evil,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:10.26,1:24:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore fell from non-linear paradise
Dialogue: 0,1:24:14.26,1:24:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to linear humanness.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:17.35,1:24:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Humanness.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:19.48,1:24:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And so what was the problem?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:21.48,1:24:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it disobedience?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:24.48,1:24:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I see it more the innate innocence within the child.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:28.55,1:24:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The snake says,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:29.55,1:24:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,eat of me,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:30.55,1:24:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and the child in the person said,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:34.55,1:24:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:35.55,1:24:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That was, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:36.55,1:24:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,it was in a woman person,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.55,1:24:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,but it has nothing to do with gender.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.55,1:24:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Because people eat of the tree of good and evil all day long.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:44.55,1:24:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,There's channels on television that specialize in that.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:48.25,1:24:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Television is specialized in it.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:51.40,1:24:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You can eat at the apple of evil hour after hour.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:56.40,1:25:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,They specialize in evil and brag about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.65,1:25:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't they?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:01.65,1:25:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,They brag about how evil they are,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:03.65,1:25:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and they're proud of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:05.69,1:25:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And as freedom of expression,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:07.69,1:25:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,evil now has equal time with goodness,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:10.69,1:25:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,just as falsehood has equal time with truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.69,1:25:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, if you're going to,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:16.39,1:25:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a fallacious statement,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:18.46,1:25:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and I've emphasized every question.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.46,1:25:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, there's no,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:21.46,1:25:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,that's idiotic on the surface of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.10,1:25:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're going to argue with falsehood,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.10,1:25:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,what is left,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.10,1:25:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, if you're going to argue with truth,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:29.10,1:25:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,what is left for you?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:31.32,1:25:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Falsehood, correct?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:34.46,1:25:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So fair and balanced means you will have truth,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.46,1:25:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and now we will have falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:39.46,1:25:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And they will be given equal time and equal validity,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.00,1:25:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we're fair and balanced.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:51.71,1:25:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So when falsehood has equal validity,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:53.71,1:25:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,gets equal time and equal play and equal emphasis as truth,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:59.71,1:26:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,then you have the fall and decline of a great empire,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.71,1:26:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,which you're seeing in America currently.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:05.71,1:26:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What you're witnessing is the fall and decline
Dialogue: 0,1:26:08.71,1:26:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,of the great empire.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:10.81,1:26:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,All great empires have come and gone.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:13.81,1:26:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So we saw the crest of this great empire,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:16.81,1:26:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and now we see its decline for the same reason,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:19.81,1:26:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,when ethics and morality
Dialogue: 0,1:26:21.81,1:26:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and the difference between good and evil
Dialogue: 0,1:26:23.81,1:26:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,are blurred,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:24.81,1:26:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,so that they are of equal credence and equal,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:26.81,1:26:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and the courts,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:27.81,1:26:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the Ninth Circuit Court of Appeals
Dialogue: 0,1:26:28.81,1:26:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,will guarantee evil legal status everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:37.96,1:26:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you see the fall and the decline of the great empire.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:40.96,1:26:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, historians say
Dialogue: 0,1:26:42.96,1:26:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that democracy lasts about two to three hundred years,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.96,1:26:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and then because, frankly,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:47.96,1:26:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,because the people below 200
Dialogue: 0,1:26:49.96,1:26:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,have an equal vote to the people above 200
Dialogue: 0,1:26:51.96,1:26:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and out-populate them,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:52.96,1:26:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,eventually,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:55.34,1:26:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the great empire,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:57.34,1:27:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,whether it's Egypt or Greece or Italy,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:01.34,1:27:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Italian Empire, Rome,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:04.63,1:27:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,all the great empires come and go.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:06.89,1:27:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We see Europe on the decline.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:09.94,1:27:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.18,1:27:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So what is the meaning of all that?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:14.18,1:27:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the multiple expressions of potentiality,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:18.18,1:27:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and of course,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:19.18,1:27:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the more energy this has,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:21.18,1:27:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the more energy this has to have to bring it down.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:25.36,1:27:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you have considerable powerful integrity,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:28.36,1:27:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,it takes some very powerful negativity to destroy it.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:31.36,1:27:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we're seeing the powerful negativity arise,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:34.36,1:27:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and you see the decline of the calibration level of America
Dialogue: 0,1:27:37.36,1:27:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and of the world in general.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:39.36,1:27:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So I think I agree with the people.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:41.65,1:27:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,There are a number of writers
Dialogue: 0,1:27:43.65,1:27:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,who write about the fall and decline
Dialogue: 0,1:27:46.65,1:27:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,of the West currently,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:48.65,1:27:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and I think they're probably correct.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:50.65,1:27:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.85,1:27:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So what about it?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:58.60,1:28:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,All things arise and all things fall.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:01.60,1:28:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,All protoplasm arises and all protoplasm returns to dust.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:05.60,1:28:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But you could say what happens then
Dialogue: 0,1:28:10.77,1:28:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,is when a thing goes down,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:12.77,1:28:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,it then triggers a reaction that brings it back up again.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:16.77,1:28:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's say consciousness arose here,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:18.77,1:28:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,went down here,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:19.77,1:28:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,this causes a reaction and now it rebounds to ever higher.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:23.77,1:28:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So I would say the calamity that arises
Dialogue: 0,1:28:26.77,1:28:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,from negating the value of truth
Dialogue: 0,1:28:29.77,1:28:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,will be so calamitous
Dialogue: 0,1:28:30.77,1:28:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,that truth will regain respectability.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:33.77,1:28:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?
